     * slots [at+1, numrows) down by one and then bumps idx on [at, numrows-2],
     * so the post-state indices are fully determined by `at`:
     *   at==0 -> row0.idx==2, row1.idx==3       (slot0 = old row1 then ++,
     *                                             slot1 = old row2 then ++)
